{
    "word": "Lollard",
    "definitions": [
        "One of a sect of early reformers in Germany.",
        "One of the followers of Wyclif in England."
    ],
    "examples": [
        "By Lollards all know the Wyclifities are meant, so called from Walter Lollardus, one of their teachers in Germany."
    ],
    "etymology": "[LL. Lollardi, Lullardi, from Walter Lolhardus, a German; cf. LG. & D. lollen to mumble, to hum, sing in a murmuring strain; hence, OD. lollaerd a mumbler, i. e., of prayers or psalms, which was prob. the origin of the name. See Loll, Lull.]"
}